the COVID 19 pandemic which has hit Ghana and the whole world. COVID 19 came as a surprise. None knew its origin and also, even none can shift the blame to anyone. We have kept moving from one stage of the pandemic to another and I believe we are in for one of the most significant test to humanity. It has shut down the world and Kuo has also experienced the all together. We have settled in our homes during the lockdown to make sure that we do not travel and participate in any activities that will expose us to the virus.

We have passed through the fire but we have come out stronger. We are still counting our losses and Ghanaians are mourning but will continue to mourn. COVID 19 is a reality that no one can understand. Never in the history of the world have we gone through this sad moment. COVID 19 has killed more than two million and four hundred thousand people (2.4M) around the world and has infected more than one hundred and twenty-five million people (125M). In Ghana, we have recorded more than two thousand deaths and also, nearly two hundred and fifty thousand (250,000) people have contracted the virus.
